	That install applies to "Rubicon" © 1992 21st Century

	That install requires WHDLoad and DIC in path (available in the WHDLoad package)
	To install from a different drive than DF0: select Expert as
	installation mode.

	You need 1.0 MB ChipMem (and 0.9 MB of any mem for PreLoad option).
	You can quit the game by pressing your default quit key

	if you have problems with this installation please try first to get
	a newer version of this install from 
		http://www.whdload.de/
	if that doesn't help try some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC,
	NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. if that also doesn't help inform the
	author via the Bug-Report-Form which can be accessed on
		http://www.whdload.de/

	for full WHDLoad package and other installs refer to:
		http://www.whdload.de/
	or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
	and	aminet:game/patch/


	Thanks to:
	-  Harry for original disk images.

    version 2.1 (10-Jul-2019):
	- forgot to perform joypad/joystick auto-detection, damn this happens too often (issue #0004152)
	
	version 2.0 (11-Jun-2019) done by JOTD
	- adapted to whdload v17
	- resourced from Bored Seal slave & Mr Larmer previous sources
	- added CD32 controls
	- added manual
	- added 2nd/button/blue for jump option
	- source code included
	
	version 1.1 (30-Jun-2002) done by Bored Seal:
	- blitter waits (5x) added
	- trainer option added (set CUSTOM1=1 for unlimited energy/lives)
	- Back to the Roots version supported (version check removed)
	- colorbit access fixed (9x)
	- original decruncher copied to expansion memory instead of being in slave
	
    version 1.0 (14-Jul-1998) by Mr.Larmer/Wanted Team
	- first public release
	- protection removed
	- bug fixed: moveq #0,D1 was lost when game set colors
	  with first title pic
	- blitter waits added (14x)
	- decruncher relocated to fast
	- nice NI/MWB icons included
	